A Spanish UN soldier and an interpreter were killed  in a road accident Sunday on patrol near Kocine, five kilometres (three miles)  southeast of Mostar, Hercegovina, Spanish defence ministry officials said.
Non-commissioned officer Fernando Casas Martin and interpreter Mirko  Mikulcic were killed while three other soldiers who were slightly injured were  transfered to the Spanish military hospital at Dracevo.
The Spanish authorities opened an enquiry to determine the cause of the  accident.
